{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_11","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] `DoD-01` Scope lock: all shipped features map to spec MVP scope; non-goals are not implemented.\n  - Evidence: scope trace in `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md`.\n- [ ] `DoD-02` Requirement traceability: every `FR-*` and `NFR-*` maps to at least one test and one evidence artifact.\n  - Evidence: trace matrix in `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-consensus.md`.\n- [ ] `DoD-03` Boilerplate reuse policy satisfied: no forbidden platform rebuilds without ADR justification.\n  - Evidence: architecture/ADR review notes and changed-file audit.\n- [ ] `DoD-04` Build gate passes on macOS lane.\n  - Test: `xcodebuild build` succeeds.\n- [ ] `DoD-05` Test gate passes on macOS lane.\n  - Test: `xcodebuild test` succeeds.\n- [ ] `DoD-06` Static quality gates pass.\n  - Test: SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan all green and blocking.\n- [ ] `DoD-07` File size and language constraints pass.\n  - Test: production and test Swift files <= 400 LOC; Swift 6 strict concurrency enforced.\n- [ ] `DoD-08` Accessibility gate passes for core flows.\n  - Test: Dynamic Type, VoiceOver labels, contrast checks, and 44x44 pt tap target verification.\n- [ ] `DoD-09` Reliability features are functional.\n  - Test: reliability ledger logs alarm timeline and failure reasons in integration tests.\n- [ ] `DoD-10` Wake contract and escalation are functional.\n  - Test: missed wake-check transitions to escalation path in automated tests.\n- [ ] `DoD-11` Adaptive mission rotation is functional.\n  - Test: automated tests validate modality coverage and anti-repeat behavior.\n- [ ] `DoD-12` First-task bridge is functional.\n  - Test: wake completion blocked until micro-task completion in UI test.\n- [ ] `DoD-13` Appium exploratory QA pass is present.\n  - Evidence: `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` with `ok=true`, `crashes=0`, `failures=0`.\n- [ ] DoD-14 Appium deferral is forbidden for this run.\n  - Rule: allow_macos_deferred=false; GitHub Actions hosted macOS iOS simulator Appium/XCUITest evidence is required, and missing evidence blocks release handoff.\n- [ ] `DoD-15` App Store 4.3 anti-clone gate passes.\n  - Test: differentiators `D-01..D-04` are present in onboarding, core flow, and store narrative.\n- [ ] `DoD-16` Privacy and secret-handling policy passes.\n  - Test: no hardcoded secrets, no credential values in logs/artifacts, only true/false presence checks.\n- [ ] `DoD-17` Release evidence bundle is complete.\n  - Evidence: CI quality report, Appium report, release-readiness notes, and final consensus verdict.\n- [ ] `DoD-18` Final review fanout has no blocking issues.\n  - Evidence: product fidelity, iOS architecture, security/privacy, code quality, QA evidence, and release readiness all approve.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_12","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Product Spec\n\n## Research Evidence\n- Evidence inputs reviewed: App Store reviews, Reddit pain mining, competitor scans, iOS design-pattern synthesis, and the quality bar contract.\n- Evidence confidence: medium-high. Signals are consistent across sources on reliability distrust, anti-autopilot need, ad friction, and relapse after dismissal.\n- Primary target user: heavy sleepers and chronic snoozers facing real-world consequences (work, school, caregiving, shift transitions).\n- Core job-to-be-done: convert `alarm fired` into `awake and executing first morning action`, not just dismissal.\n\n## User Journeys\n- `J-01 Critical Wake`: User creates a strict alarm with mission stack, alarm fires, user completes adaptive mission, passes wake-check, completes first micro-task, and sees reliability timeline entry.\n- `J-02 Relapse Recovery`: User dismisses but ignores wake-check; app escalates (configured louder pattern / repeat challenge), requires re-validation, logs escalation outcome.\n- `J-03 Trust Verification`: User opens reliability ledger and sees per-alarm timeline: scheduled, triggered, mission completion, wake-check status, escalation/failure reason.\n- `J-04 Fast Setup`: New user completes setup wizard with iOS constraint disclosure, permission rationale, and privacy explanation before first alarm activation.\n\n## MVP Scope\n- In scope:\n  - Alarm creation/editing with mission stack and strictness level.\n  - Adaptive mission rotation across at least 3 modalities: cognitive, movement, scan/photo/object.\n  - Post-dismiss wake-check contract with configurable window and escalation.\n  - Reliability ledger with human-readable per-alarm execution logs.\n  - First-task bridge: one user-selected micro-task required after wake verification.\n  - Ad-free critical wake path (active alarm + immediate post-dismiss + wake-check).\n  - Basic weekly wake consistency summary.\n- Non-goals:\n  - Sleep-stage tracking platform.\n  - Public social feed or stranger accountability mechanics.\n  - Wellness content library (stories/sounds/coaching).\n  - Wearable-dependent launch requirements.\n\n## Boilerplate Reuse\n- Base: extend `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` in `apps/waketask-iphone`; no platform rebuild.\n- Mandatory policy: extend before replace.\n- Rebuilds forbidden without ADR-level justification: auth, payments, AI, storage, networking, localization, settings, design system, DI/composition root.\n- Any proposed net-new infrastructure must include:\n  - Existing module evaluated.\n  - Gap found.\n  - Why extension is not viable.\n  - Replacement cost/benefit and App Store 4.3 impact.\n\n## Design Direction\n- Product tone: calm, serious, high-trust; avoid gimmick and shame framing.\n- UX priorities:\n  - Single clear next action during active alarm.\n  - Large controls, high legibility, high contrast, clear countdown/status.\n  - No monetization interruptions in critical wake path.\n  - Explicit privacy copy for on-device mission validation.\n- Differentiation Contract (4.3 hardening):\n  - `D-01` Reliability ledger is visible and usable in first session.\n  - `D-02` Post-dismiss wake-check escalation is active and configurable.\n  - `D-03` Adaptive anti-autopilot mission rotation changes mission pattern over time.\n  - `D-04` First-task bridge is integrated into wake completion flow.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- `FR-01 Alarm Setup`: User can create, edit, enable, disable alarms with mission stack and strictness.\n  - Verification: UI test creates and edits alarm; persisted state reload confirms values.\n- `FR-02 Mission Engine`: App supports at least 3 mission modalities and rotation logic.\n  - Verification: unit tests validate modality selection and anti-repeat rules.\n- `FR-03 Wake Contract`: Dismissal requires wake-check within configured window; missed check triggers escalation.\n  - Verification: integration test with mocked time path asserts escalation state transition.\n- `FR-04 Reliability Ledger`: Each alarm run writes timeline records with success/failure reason.\n  - Verification: repository integration test asserts schema fields and ordering.\n- `FR-05 First-Task Bridge`: Wake flow is incomplete until selected micro-task marked complete.\n  - Verification: UI test blocks completion until first task done.\n- `FR-06 Ad-Free Critical Path`: No interstitial ads in alarm, dismiss, wake-check flows.\n  - Verification: release audit checklist plus automated string scan for ad-sdk entrypoints in critical flow module.\n- `NFR-01 Performance`: cold launch p95 <= 2.0s on target simulator profile.\n  - Verification: startup metric capture in CI report.\n- `NFR-02 Interaction Latency`: mission interaction response p95 <= 200ms.\n  - Verification: UI performance test with 30 sampled actions.\n- `NFR-03 Stability`: crash-free sessions >= 99.5% in pre-release test runs.\n  - Verification: Appium exploratory + XCTest run logs with crash count = 0 for gate pass.\n- `NFR-04 Accessibility`: Dynamic Type, VoiceOver labels, contrast >= WCAG AA, tap targets >= 44x44 pt for core flows.\n  - Verification: accessibility audit checklist + XCTest assertions where automatable.\n- `NFR-05 Privacy/Data`: mission validation data processed on-device for MVP; no secret values logged.\n  - Verification: code review plus log scan gate with zero violations.\n- `NFR-06 File/Code Quality`: Swift production and test files remain <= 400 lines; Swift 6 strict concurrency preserved.\n  - Verification: lint/build gate and line-count script in CI.\n\n## Appium Exploratory QA\n- Required artifact: `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`.\n- Pass conditions:\n  - Real simulator/Appium/XCUITest run executed.\n  - `buttons_tapped > 0` and representative coverage of all reachable MVP screens.\n  - `crashes = 0`, `failures = 0`.\n- Required report fields:\n  - `ok`, `buttons_tapped`, `screens_visited`, `crashes`, `failures`, `failures_detail`.\n- Deferral policy:\n  - For this run, deferral is not allowed: allow_macos_deferred=false.\n  - Appium/XCUITest exploratory evidence must come from GitHub Actions hosted macOS iOS simulator evidence.\n  - Local simulator limitations and human testing are not acceptance evidence tonight.\n  - Missing Appium evidence blocks release handoff.\n\n## App Store Readiness\n- 4.3 anti-clone gate must pass:\n  - Differentiation contract (`D-01`..`D-04`) is visible in onboarding, core wake flow, and metadata/screenshots narrative.\n  - Release strings and metadata must not read as generic template alarm clone copy.\n- Compliance and release evidence must include:\n  - `xcodebuild build` pass.\n  - `xcodebuild test` pass.\n  - SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, and secret scan all pass as blocking gates.\n  - Privacy disclosures align with actual data behavior.\n- Security handling:\n  - Credential checks are true/false presence only.\n  - No printing/logging/writing of secret values in artifacts.\n\n## Definition of Done\n- Canonical DoD is maintained in `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md` and is release-blocking.\n- `Done` requires every checklist item to be verifiably satisfied with evidence artifacts.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-consensus.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Implementation Review Consensus\n\n## Inputs Read\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-correctness.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-tests.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-security.md`\n- `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-boilerplate.md`\n\n## Reviewer Agreement and Disagreement\n- Agreement: all four reviews approve integration scope, with no blocking defects in implemented wiring.\n- Agreement: macOS-hosted CI execution remains required for final release signoff evidence.\n- Disagreement: none; reviewers converged on non-blocking residual execution risk only.\n\n## Blocking Issues\n- None in implementation content for the integration phase.\n- Residual risk (non-blocking for review merge): hosted macOS simulator execution evidence must still be produced by CI.\n\n## Concrete Retry Target\n- Run text-gate verification against this file using the standard pass/fail regex pair.\n- Execute macOS CI lane to produce fresh `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` and `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` artifacts from runner evidence.\n\n## Simplification Instructions\n- No simplification required. Scope remained integration-only and additive to boilerplate.\n\nVERDICT: APPROVED\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md\"","aggregated_output":"# WakeTask Architecture (SwiftAIBoilerplatePro-Mapped)\n\n## Purpose\nThis architecture implements WakeTask by extending `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro` and preserving boilerplate infrastructure boundaries required by the spec, DoD, and quality bar.\n\n## Product-to-Boilerplate Mapping\n\n| Boilerplate Module | WakeTask Use | Action |\n|---|---|---|\n| `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj` | Primary app target, test targets, package wiring, CI entrypoint | Keep; extend target dependencies and schemes only as needed |\n| `Config/App.xcconfig` | App identity, build settings, flags for wake contract/escalation, test toggles | Keep; add WakeTask-specific keys via additive config |\n| `Packages/Core` | Domain models and use-cases: alarms, mission stack, wake contract, reliability ledger, first-task bridge | Extend heavily (new entities/services/use-cases) |\n| `Packages/Networking` | Remote config and optional telemetry transport outside critical wake path | Keep; minimal extension, no critical-flow hard dependency |\n| `Packages/Storage` | Local persistence for alarms, runs, mission outcomes, escalation timeline | Extend with WakeTask repositories and migrations |\n| `Packages/Auth` | Optional account identity/sync readiness, not required for MVP wake flow | Keep; no rebuild, mostly unchanged for MVP |\n| `Packages/Payments` | Subscription/paywall handling outside active wake path | Keep; strict separation from critical wake path |\n| `Packages/AI` | Adaptive mission rotation heuristics and anti-repeat policy support | Extend using existing AI abstractions |\n| `Packages/FeatureSettings` | Strictness, wake-check window, escalation profile, ad-free critical-path toggles | Extend with WakeTask settings surfaces |\n| `Packages/Localization` | User-facing wake flow copy, trust/privacy copy, ledger language | Extend string tables and localized resources |\n| `Packages/DesignSystem` | High-legibility controls, contrast-safe theming, large touch targets | Extend components/tokens; preserve DS conventions |\n| `CompositionRoot` | Dependency assembly: repositories, mission engine, wake-check scheduler, app shell routes | Extend factory wiring and environment injection |\n\n## Layering and Dependency Order\n1. `Config/App.xcconfig` and target settings establish compile-time flags.\n2. `Packages/Core` defines domain protocols/entities and use-cases.\n3. `Packages/Storage` and `Packages/Networking` implement infra adapters consumed by Core-facing repositories.\n4. `Packages/AI` provides mission-selection policy services consumed by Core.\n5. `Packages/Auth` and `Packages/Payments` stay optional integrations and must not block alarm execution.\n6. `Packages/FeatureSettings` and `Packages/Localization` provide runtime configuration and language resources for UI flows.\n7. `Packages/DesignSystem` renders all WakeTask UI surfaces with accessibility constraints.\n8. `CompositionRoot` composes implementations and injects view model dependencies into app flows in `SwiftAIBoilerplatePro`.\n\n## WakeTask Feature Architecture\n- Alarm Domain (`Core` + `Storage`): create/edit/enable alarms, strictness, mission stack persistence.\n- Mission Engine (`Core` + `AI`): select rotating modalities (cognitive/movement/scan-photo), anti-repeat safeguards.\n- Wake Contract (`Core` + scheduler infra): dismissal requires wake-check deadline; misses trigger escalation state.\n- Reliability Ledger (`Core` + `Storage`): append-only alarm-run timeline with success/failure reasons.\n- First-Task Bridge (`Core` + app shell UI): completion gate until first micro-task done.\n- Settings and Policy (`FeatureSettings`): user-configurable wake-check windows/escalation.\n\n## UI and Composition\n- App shell routes are extended to include onboarding, alarm setup, active alarm, wake-check, reliability ledger, and weekly consistency summary.\n- UI state lives in feature-specific view models; business rules stay in `Core` use-cases.\n- `DesignSystem` governs typography, spacing, color contrast, and min 44x44 pt interactions for all MVP flows.\n\n## Concurrency and Reliability\n- Swift 6 strict concurrency remains enabled.\n- Long-running wake timers/escalation scheduling use actor-safe state coordination and structured task cancellation.\n- Critical wake path avoids network hard dependencies; local storage is source of truth for wake execution.\n\n## Testing and Quality Gates\n- Unit tests: mission rotation logic, anti-repeat policy, wake-check deadline transitions.\n- Integration tests: persistence schema/order for reliability ledger entries.\n- UI tests: alarm setup/edit and first-task completion gate.\n- Performance tests: launch p95 <= 2.0s, mission interaction p95 <= 200ms.\n- Accessibility checks: Dynamic Type, VoiceOver labels, contrast AA, 44x44 targets.\n- CI gates: `xcodebuild build`, `xcodebuild test`, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan.\n- Exploratory QA: required Appium/XCUITest report at `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`.\n- Appium evidence source: hosted GitHub Actions macOS iOS simulator. allow_macos_deferred=false; local simulator limits and human testing are not acceptance evidence.\n\n## Non-Goals and Guardrails\n- No rebuild of auth/payments/AI/storage/networking/localization/settings/design system/DI.\n- No monetization interruptions in active alarm, dismiss, or wake-check flow.\n- No feature additions that violate MVP non-goals (sleep-stage platform, social feed, wearable dependency).\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
