ss|WakeMission\" apps/waketask-iphone/Packages apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro -g '*.swift'`\n- `sed -n '1,240p' apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/en.lproj/Localizable.strings`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`\n- `sed -n '1,220p' apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/AppRootView.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/WakeTask/WakeTaskModels.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Previews/PreviewComposition.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,320p' apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Previews/PreviewMocks.swift`\n- `sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/es.lproj/Localizable.strings`\n- `cat <<'EOF' >> apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Localization/Sources/Localization/Resources/es.lproj/Localizable.strings ... EOF`\n- `rg -n \"bodySemibold|statusError|wakeFlowViewModel|L10n.Wake|wakeAddAlarmButton|wakeAlarmCell\" apps/waketask-iphone -g '*.swift'`\n- `cd apps/waketask-iphone && xcodebuild -list -project SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj | head -n 80`\n- `git -C /home/daytona/workspace diff --name-only`\n- `git -C /home/daytona/workspace status --short apps/waketask-iphone | sed -n '1,120p'`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- Implemented real WakeTask interface flow (alarm list, new alarm creation, strictness selection, start run, mission completion, wake-check, first-task completion, dismiss) in `WakeDashboardView` using existing `WakeFlowViewModel` and AppShell navigation.\n- Preserved existing app shell and navigation structure; integrated wake interface through `MainTabView` and `AppRootView` with CompositionRoot factory usage.\n- Used DesignSystem tokens/components in the new interface (colors, typography, spacing).\n- Localized all newly user-visible strings through `Localization` (`L10n.Wake`) with English and Spanish resource entries.\n- Added accessibility labels/hints/identifiers to tappable controls in the new interface, including alarm actions, run actions, form actions, and mission controls.\n- Added explicit accessibility identifiers for discoverability by exploratory automation on key controls and cells:\n  - `wakeAddAlarmButton`\n  - `wakeAlarmCell-*`\n  - `wakeStartRunButton-*`\n  - `wakeMissionButton-*`\n  - `wakeCompleteWakeCheckButton`\n  - `wakeCompleteFirstTaskButton`\n  - `wakeDismissAlarmButton`\n  - `wakeAlarmNameField`, `wakeAlarmTimePicker`, `wakeStrictnessPicker`, `wakeFirstTaskField`\n\n## Risks\n- Full iOS build/test could not be executed in this environment because `xcodebuild` is not installed here; compile/runtime verification must run on macOS/Xcode.\n- Existing `es.lproj/Localizable.strings` contains invalid UTF-8 bytes from prior state; new keys were appended safely, but a normalization pass may be needed to avoid future tooling issues.\n- The repository’s Appium tapper script is currently a placeholder and does not execute simulator traversal yet; identifiers are prepared, but hosted macOS traversal still needs to run to validate discovery end-to-end.\n\n## Verifier notes\n- Verified phase scope stayed within interface concerns: AppShell tab/root wiring, Wake UI surface, previews, and localization resources only.\n- Evidence includes required artifacts: concrete file list, explicit commands, acceptance criteria, and risks.\n- Boilerplate conventions were preserved: dependency construction remains in `CompositionRoot`/`AppEnvironment`, strings are routed via `L10n.Wake`, and UI styling uses `DesignSystem` tokens.\n- No quality gate was silently weakened or deferred; the only deferred checks (full Xcode build/runtime traversal) are explicitly documented with rationale.\n- Generated code remains modular and testable: `WakeDashboardView` depends on injected `WakeFlowViewModel`, and preview mocks support isolated UI verification.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
