test` in `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage`\n- `git -C /home/daytona/workspace status --short`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- Domain models added for alarms, mission modalities, strictness, wake runs, and append-only reliability ledger events.\n- Core mission rotation engine added with anti-repeat behavior that adapts by strictness and is unit-tested.\n- Wake contract evaluator added for dismiss/wake-check/escalation/first-task transitions and unit-tested.\n- Local persistence implemented with privacy-preserving JSON store (local-only, no secret logging) for alarms and wake runs via repositories.\n- ViewModel logic implemented (`WakeFlowViewModel`) covering alarm CRUD toggles, mission completion, wake-check enforcement, escalation evaluation, first-task bridge, and weekly consistency.\n- CompositionRoot wired with wake repositories + mission engine and a factory for wake flow ViewModel.\n- Unit tests added for Core logic, Storage repositories, and ViewModel behavior (including escalation and completion gating).\n\n## Risks\n- Swift toolchain is unavailable in this environment (`swift` command is not present), so test execution output cannot be captured here.\n- Current core integration is logic/DI level only; UI wiring for alarm setup, active alarm, wake-check, and ledger surfaces remains for later phases.\n- JSON local store is single-file persistence; future migrations/versioning may be needed when schema evolves.\n\n## Verifier notes\n- Scope check passed: changes stay within Core/Storage/AppShell wake-domain logic plus DI wiring and tests; no out-of-phase product surface expansion detected.\n- Evidence completeness passed: file list, commands, acceptance criteria, and risks are present and aligned with touched artifacts.\n- Boilerplate convention check passed: wake dependencies are injected via `CompositionRoot` and factory methods (`makeWakeFlowViewModel()`), with protocol-driven repositories/engine keeping modules testable.\n- Quality-gate integrity check passed: no gate weakening/deferment found; environment constraint around local Swift toolchain is documented in Risks.\n- Testability/modularity check passed: wake logic is split across models/protocols/engine/evaluator/store/view-model layers with unit tests in Core, Storage, and app target.\n- 2026-05-14 independent verifier pass: sampled `CompositionRoot`, `CompositionRoot+Factories`, `WakeFlowViewModel`, protocol boundaries, and local repository implementations; evidence and code remain consistent with core-phase scope.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
