{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_19","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/integration.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Integration Phase Evidence\n\n## Files changed\n- apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Composition/CompositionRoot+Factories.swift\n- apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/AppRootView.swift\n- apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplateProUITests/IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests.swift\n- apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplateProTests/CompositionRootTests.swift\n- apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh\n- apps/waketask-iphone/.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml\n- apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh\n- apps/waketask-iphone/docs/maintenance/IOS_QUALITY_READINESS.md\n- apps/waketask-iphone/.qlty/qlty.toml\n\n## Commands run\n- `sed -n` inspections for AppShell, CompositionRoot, UI tests, CI scripts, and workflow files\n- `rg -n` inspections for quality gates, auth bypass fixture usage, and readiness docs\n- `bash -n apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh`\n- `bash -n apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`\n- `chmod +x apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh apps/waketask-iphone/scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- WakeTask flow is wired through AppShell and CompositionRoot factories used by `AppRootView` and `MainTabView`.\n- Integration UI fixture covers wake traversal in `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests` with `AUTH_BYPASS=1` for deterministic navigation.\n- Unit coverage includes wake factory construction in `CompositionRootTests`.\n- `scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh` includes required gates: xcodebuild build/test, SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, and App Store string audit.\n- Secret handling is redacted to presence state only (`present=true|false`) with no secret value output.\n- `.github/workflows/ios-quality.yml` runs CI quality + exploratory automation and uploads both report artifacts.\n- `scripts/qa/appium-exploratory-tapper.sh` writes `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` after successful exploratory run.\n- `scripts/ci/ios-quality.sh` writes `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json` after all quality checks are green.\n- Release/readiness guidance is documented in `docs/maintenance/IOS_QUALITY_READINESS.md`.\n\n## Risks\n- Full xcodebuild execution requires a macOS runner with Xcode and iOS Simulator runtime.\n- App Store string audit uses strict template-token matching and may need allowlist tuning if product copy intentionally overlaps template phrases.\n\n## Verifier notes\n- Integration and release-hardening scope is complete and constrained to requested areas.\n- Quality gates are explicit and enforced before report emission.\n- Secret handling policy is implemented with redacted presence-only logging.\n- Evidence structure includes all required sections for phase gating.\n- Re-verified on 2026-05-14: integration gate snapshot at `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/evidence/integration-gate.json` is `ok: true` with no failures.\n- Generated code remains modular/testable: factory-based DI in `CompositionRoot+Factories`, explicit UI integration coverage in `IntegrationWakeExploratoryUITests`, and composition factory unit coverage in `CompositionRootTests`.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
