{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > /home/daytona/workspace/.workflow/iphone-app-factory/reviews/implementation-correctness.md <<'EOF'\n# Implementation Correctness Review\n\n## Scope\n- Reviewed \"'`.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec.md`, `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/definition-of-done.md`, `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/architecture.md`, phase evidence (`foundation/core/interface/integration`), and WakeTask implementation in `apps/waketask-iphone`.\n- Focused on correctness against product requirements (FR-01..FR-06, D-01..D-04), not just presence of artifacts.\n\n## Findings\n\n### blocking: FR-01 Alarm setup is incomplete (no alarm edit flow)\n- Requirement: `FR-01` requires create, edit, enable, disable alarms.\n- Current implementation supports create and enable/disable only.\n- `WakeFlowViewModel` has `createAlarm` and `setAlarmEnabled`, but no update/edit API for title/time/strictness/first-task on existing alarms.\n- `WakeDashboardView` exposes create sheet and toggle; no edit affordance per alarm row.\n- Evidence:\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeFlowViewModel.swift`\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift`\n\n### blocking: FR-03 wake-check escalation is not actively enforced by runtime flow\n- Requirement: missed wake-check must trigger escalation path (active contract behavior, not only helper method existence).\n- `WakeFlowViewModel.evaluateEscalationIfNeeded()` exists but is never invoked from UI lifecycle/timer/background check after dismissal.\n- In `WakeDashboardView`, no task/timer calls escalation evaluator while run is awaiting check.\n- Result: escalation can remain dormant unless a caller manually triggers `evaluateEscalationIfNeeded`, which breaks the required wake contract behavior.\n- Evidence:\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeFlowViewModel.swift`\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift`\n\n### blocking: FR-04 and D-01 reliability ledger is not visible/usable in product UI\n- Requirement: reliability ledger with per-alarm timeline records, visible and usable in first session (`D-01`).\n- Data model/event logging exists in `WakeRun.events`, but there is no ledger screen or timeline UI showing historical run events/reasons.\n- `WakeDashboardView` only shows active run controls and weekly consistency percentage; prior run timeline is absent.\n- Onboarding copy claims timeline availability, but no corresponding usable view is implemented.\n- Evidence:\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Core/Sources/Core/WakeTask/WakeTaskModels.swift`\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/Wake/WakeDashboardView.swift`\n  - `apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/AppShell/OnboardingPage.swift`\n\n### non-blocking: exploratory evidence file location mismatch in this workspace snapshot\n- `appium-exploratory-report.json` is required by spec/DoD and referenced as present in earlier stage logs, but not present at `apps/waketask-iphone/reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` in this checkout.\n- This may be an artifact sync/state issue rather than product logic defect.\n\n## Requirement Mapping Summary\n- `FR-01`: **failed** (missing edit flow).\n- `FR-02`: **pass** (3 modalities + rotation logic implemented).\n- `FR-03`: **failed** (escalation not automatically enforced by runtime UI flow).\n- `FR-04`: **failed** (ledger data exists, but ledger UX missing).\n- `FR-05`: **partial/pass** (run completion gated on wake-check + first task in evaluator; no contradiction found).\n- `FR-06`: **pass** from implementation inspection (no ad insertion in wake critical path).\n- `D-01`: **failed** (ledger not usable in first session).\n- `D-02`: **partial** (dismiss/wake-check exists; escalation configurability not clearly surfaced).\n- `D-03`: **pass** (mission rotation and anti-repeat implemented).\n- `D-04`: **pass** (first-task completion integrated into completion logic).\n\n## Verdict\nVERDICT: REJECTED\n\nImplementation should return to execution before simplification, with priority on:\n1. Add full alarm edit flow (view model + UI + tests).\n2. Make wake-check escalation automatically evaluated/enforced in runtime flow.\n3. Implement a user-visible reliability ledger timeline for alarm runs, including success/failure/escalation reasons.\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
